RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 11 6F Dirt CR: 102. Claiming Purse 56000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since March 4 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOLIDIFY got hung in the six path while far back, drifted to the eight path entering the lane, yet sustained a rally while gradually shifting in, bid leaving the furlong grounds, and edged ahead. LEGAL DEAL tracked in the two path and between horses, altered course outside of the leaders in midstretch, and rallied to gain place at the wire. HOOPERDRIVESTHBOAT rushed to vie along the inside, chased his outer counterpart into and around the turn, kept on through the lane to gain place in the closing stages, but got nailed at the wire. EMERALD EXPRESS broke slowly, trailed in the two path, advanced between horses while hanging on his left lead in midstretch, then rallied between the top flight late. ALL EYES WEST tracked in the four path, chased on his left lead in upper stretch, got outkicked at the furlong grounds, and kept on mildly. RACE DRIVER was washed out pre-race, stalked the leader from the three path, bid turning for home, dueled through midstretch, but weakened between horses at the sixteenth pole. DARK TIMBER set the pace in the two path, dueled inside of an outer bidder in upper stretch, but faltered between horses entering the final sixteenth. PALACE KITTEN never got involved from the two path. CRIME SPREE made little impact from the five path. BOISE lacked speed in the three path and between horses, and got outrun. THE RIDER OF SOLIDIFY CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE WINNER FOR INTERFERENCE IN MIDSTRETCH, BUT THE OBJECTION WAS DISALLOWED BY THE STEWARDS
